=====================================================================
SUBNET AUR GATEWAY KA ROLE
=====================================================================

Jab bhi device ko kisi destination IP par packet bhejna hota hai,
to sabse pehle wo check karta hai:

"Kya ye destination IP mere local network me hai?"

Yahan subnet mask use hota hai.

SUBNET MASK ka role :

It decides whether destination IP is:

        ✔ LOCAL
               OR
        ✔ OUTSIDE NETWORK


Agar destination IP:
same/local network me hai  -> packet directly local network me bheja jayega via ARP


Agar destination IP:
local network ke bahar hai -> packet gateway ko bheja jayega

-----------------
GATEWAY ka role:
-----------------

Device/laptop ke perspective se:

    "Jo bhi traffic mere local network ke bahar hai,
     use mujhe is IP ko bhejna hai."


Matlab:
device non-local traffic gateway ko forward karta hai.


Home networks me usually:

    gateway = router ka local/private IP

=====================================================================
IMPORTANT
=====================================================================

Gateway aur router(private IP)
zaruri nahi ki hamesha same cheez ho.


Gateway:
wo next-hop / exit point hota hai
jiske paas device non-local traffic bhejta hai.


Router:
network traffic ko different networks ke beech route karta hai.


Home networks me usually:
same router device hi gateway ka role perform karta hai.

Isliye ghar ke networks me:
router aur gateway same lagte hain.


But enterprise/cloud environments me:
gateway aur actual internet router alag devices ho sakte hain.


Example:

    PC
      ->
    Firewall
      ->
    Router
      ->
    Internet


Is case me:

    PC ka default gateway:
        firewall ho sakta hai,
        NOT actual internet router.

