CASE 1 : DNS SERVER = 192.168.1.1
=====================================================================

Example:

DHCP ne DNS server diya:

    DNS Server:
        192.168.1.1

    Subnet Mask:
        255.255.255.0


Ab laptop DNS request bhejna chahta hai:

    192.168.1.5
            ->
    192.168.1.1


Laptop subnet mask check karta hai aur conclude karta hai:

    "192.168.1.1 same local network me hai."


IS CASE ME KYA HOGA?

    ✔ destination local hai
    ✔ gateway use nahi hoga
    ✔ packet directly local network me bheja jayega


Lekin local network me packet bhejne ke liye
laptop ko destination device ka MAC address chahiye.


Isliye laptop ARP broadcast bhejta hai:

    "Who has 192.168.1.1 ?
     Tell 192.168.1.5"


Router reply karta hai:

    "192.168.1.1 is me.
     My MAC is:
     AA:BB:CC:DD"


Ab laptop actual DNS request send karta hai.

IMPORTANT:

Laptop:
- IP packet aur Ethernet/WiFi frame separately nahi bhejta
- balki multiple layers ko ek dusre ke andar wrap/encapsulate karta hai

