UDP SEGMENT KYA HOTA HAI?

DNS usually UDP protocol use karta hai.

UDP ka full form: User Datagram Protocol

UDP transport layer protocol hai.

Ye:
- source port
- destination port

maintain karta hai so that OS ko pata chale:

    "Ye data kis application/process ke liye hai?"


Example:

    Source Port:
        53000

    Destination Port:
        53

Yahan:

    53000 = temporary client port assigned by OS to laptop

    53  = DNS server ka well-known port


Router fir:

    - frame receive karta hai
    - Ethernet / MAC header remove karta hai
    - IP packet inspect karta hai
    - routing table check karta hai
    - next-hop decide karta hai
    - new frame bana kar internet me forward karta hai

IMPORTANT:

MAC change hota rehta hai every hop
IP mostly same rehta hai

Example:

Laptop → Router:

Src MAC = Laptop
Dst MAC = Router

Router → ISP:

Src MAC = Router
Dst MAC = ISP Next Hop


Yahan router:
    - DNS Forwarder
    - DNS Cache

ka kaam karta hai.

Matlab:

router DNS request ko actual upstream DNS servers:

    - Google DNS
    - ISP DNS
    - Cloudflare DNS

etc. ko forward karta hai.


IMPORTANT UNDERSTANDING

Yahan router simply ek local device ki tarah act kar raha hai.

Kyuki:

    192.168.1.1

same subnet me hai.


