3. ROUTER DOES PAT (Port Address Translation)
=====================================================================

People casually "NAT" bol dete hain.

But technically:

NAT
= only IP translation

PAT
= IP + Port translation


Home routers usually PAT use karte hain because:
multiple devices same public IP share karte hain.


BEFORE PAT

    192.168.1.5:53000
            │
            ▼
      8.8.8.8:53


AFTER PAT

    49.205.10.20:61000
            │
            ▼
       8.8.8.8:53


Yahan router:
- private IP replace karta hai apne public IP se
- source port bhi remap karta hai


