6. WHY TCP IS NEEDED?
=====================================================================

Internet is somewhat unreliable.


Internet par packets:
- lost ho sakte hain
- duplicate ho sakte hain
- wrong order me pahunch sakte hain


                    INTERNET

    Packet 1   ❌ Lost
    Packet 2   ✅ Received
    Packet 3   ✅ Received


Example:

Agar browser HTML page download kar raha hai:

Packet 1
Packet 2
Packet 3


Possible hai:
- Packet 2 lost ho jaye
- Packet 3 pehle aa jaye
- Packet duplicate ho jaye


Agar reliable protocol na ho,
to webpage corrupt ho sakta hai.


Isi problem ko solve karta hai TCP.


TCP = Transmission Control Protocol


TCP provide karta hai:

1. Reliable delivery
   -> lost packet dubara mangta hai

2. Ordered delivery
   -> packets correct sequence me arrange karta hai

3. Error checking
   -> corrupted packet detect karta hai

4. Flow control
   -> sender ko control karta hai ki kitna fast bhejna hai

5. Congestion control
   -> internet overload hone se bachata hai


Isliye:
HTTP/HTTPS usually TCP use karte hain.


=====================================================================
7. TCP HANDSHAKE (VERY IMPORTANT)
=====================================================================

HTTP/HTTPS directly start nahi hota.

Sabse pehle:
TCP connection establish hota hai.


TCP ek connection-oriented protocol hai.

Matlab:
communication start hone se pehle
client aur server ek reliable connection establish karte hain.


Is process ko:
TCP 3-way handshake bolte hain.


                    TCP 3-WAY HANDSHAKE


    CLIENT                         SERVER

      SYN        ───────────────▶

                  ◀───────────────  SYN-ACK

      ACK        ───────────────▶


Ab:
TCP connection successfully establish ho gaya.


=====================================================================
8. TLS HANDSHAKE (HTTPS SECURITY LAYER)
=====================================================================

TCP establish hone ke baad:

TLS handshake hota hai.


TLS = Transport Layer Security

Ye encryption provide karta hai.


TLS ensure karta hai:
- data encrypted ho
- hacker packets sniff kare to bhi read na kar sake
- server genuine ho


TLS handshake me:
- certificates exchange hote hain
- encryption algorithms decide hote hain
- session keys generate hoti hain


CONNECTION STACK

        TCP Handshake
                ↓
        TLS Handshake
                ↓
      Encrypted HTTPS Traffic


IMPORTANT:

HTTPS actually:

HTTP + TLS hota hai.


